items.name: Luna (from "Darkness Rises")
items.description:
Works great with CarDos Animated and ReV Animated.

A LoRA model of Luna, the character of the Archer class from the now-defunct mobile game Darkness Rises developed by Boolean Games and published by NEXON. The character in question was modeled by 3D artist Soo Hwang.

The dataset was comprised of 64 renders covering most of the angles possible of her in-game model made by myself using Blender, and 42 extra images from both development behind-the-scenes footage and promo screenshots, all properly touched up and with no JPEG compression. My renders were mostly focused on her face and upper body with different hair models, so the range should be very good when it comes to that.

Please use the "darknessrises-luna" trigger word.

Her base costume is made out of a frilled bra and panties. If you keep getting that in your generations, try adding (frilled bra, frilled panties:1.4) to your negative prompt.

A good chunk of the images had a grey gradient background. If you keep getting that in your generations, try adding (grey background, simple background, gradient background:1.4) to your prompt.

These two scenarios shouldn't happen often if you specify what you want for clothing and background beforehand, but still, I'll leave this info here just in case.

While I do recommend CarDos Animated as it was the one I used to make the previews, I do encourage you to try this out with other models. It kinda works with AOM3, but you need to make your prompt steer into a more rendered look for her features to be well-defined.

Something I also noticed is that using (3d, photorealistic) makes her face stick closer to her original proportions. I didn't specify an art style during training so I have no idea why this is the case, but apart from a single image (the one where the hoodie is halfway over her head), none of the preview images had those words.

If you're having trouble getting it to look right and the LoRA is overstepping its boundaries into the rest of the scene, here's what I usually do:

  • Generate a base image at 512x with the LoRA weight set to 0.3

  • Inpaint just the face with the weight set to 0.6-0.8

  • Upscale with a low denoising value and the weight set to 0.3 again.

  • Keep inpainting with different denoising and weight values until I get the look I want.

You can either let the face keep the "gamey" look or let the model run freely over it while retaining the overall shape of her face, but you'll need to know your way around inpainting, denoising, and all that good stuff for that.

items.name: Guitars - Electric and Acoustic (Lycoris)
items.description:
This model is trained on a dataset of about ~50 or so images of anime/illustrated guitars, both electric and acoustic. The goal is to allow the user to make guitars reliably without having to do a lot of work. I've had a lot of issues with generating guitars on my own and hope this helps anyone interested as well!

The model was trained on Kenshi due to its versatility, but the images posted were generated on several different models, including AbyssOrangeMix and MeinaMix. How should we define the character of Holo? By its art style? By its characteristics? By its outfit? Or by all of them? I am confused. If I only consider the characteristics of Holo, I would rate this model as 100/100. Vice versa, since I did not bake in any art style in order to keep the compatibility of this LoCon model, if I want the same art style as the Spice & Wolf manga or novel illustrations, I would rate it 10/100.

I find myself confused by this. While the model does an excellent job of capturing Holo's characteristics, I did not include any specific art style in order to keep the model generalizable.

items.name: Album Cover Art
items.description:
A model that can generate beautiful and well-designed album covers. You can generate an album cover by describing the content of your album, the emotions it expresses, and even the genre of music. However, the biggest issue currently is the lack of control over the generated text. I am unsure of how to apply this to practical situations, which is why I hope to upload this model to the community and receive more feedback and suggestions.

Prompt & Configure

My personal recommendation is to use Euler a with 40 steps and a CFG scale of 5.5. However, you can certainly try different parameters which will yield very different effects while still maintaining a sense of design.

Here are some potentially useful keywords:

dreamy clean creepy surreal noisy soft happy sad gradient dark emotional lonely abstract sci-fi gloomy weird minimalist scary glowing glitch blur cool cold drip flex dope retro vintage plastic packaging texture sweet damaged texture simple light fashion chill lo-fi vaporwave photography depress hopeless love

Examples

prompt: A fashion album cover art with a stylish image of a model and modern typography, in the style of electronic music.

prompt: A happy album cover art with a colorful illustration of a party and playful typography, in the style of pop music.

prompt: A retro album cover art with a vintage image of a car and retro typography, in the style of rock music.

prompt: A drip album cover art with a liquid image and bold typography, in the style of electronic music.

prompt: An abstract album cover art with a geometric pattern and a bold color scheme of red and black, in the style of electronic music.

prompt: A noisy album cover art with a glitch effect and a vibrant color scheme of pink and yellow, in the style of electronic music.

Enjoy it! And feedback and suggestions are always welcome from me.

items.name: Gothic Nightclub Dark Wave Electro Party
items.description:
There is a dark wave, electro, gothic nightclub lost in time, long before the advent of social media, when images used to accumulate in galleries and pages of the web 1.0. This checkpoint was trained on images from the age of the first mass-market digital cameras 30 years ago until 15 years later. The source material has been a blurry mess of low-resolution images with lots of JPEG artefacts; they’ve all been pre-processed over several iterations with different AI upscaling and artefact removal as well as face restoration systems.

The training data from 13025 images have been blended during the training process as additions to the already present similar subjects of the SD 1.5 checkpoint. A subset of the images was already in the original low-resolution versions included in SD 1.5. The result is that this checkpoint is trained to visualise epic and surreal dark wave, electro, and gothic party scenes populated with guests and visitors wearing elaborate costumes and unique clothing with the right make-up to go along for the occasion.

The training has been set up to get the general art and a static look and feel of the dataset transferred into a versatile SD 1.5 checkpoint where everything else is preserved to allow for a wide range of subjects and compositions. The checkpoint is not trained to replicate the actual persons or a precise subset of the training data. The training took 50 epochs over 1630240 iterations.

Use “GothClub2K” in your prompts to invoke attention to the training data and dataset of the subjects alongside a detailed description of what you like to visualise.

SeaArt GhostMix model at: 海艺 (seaart.ai)

IMPORTANT MATTERS(重要事项)

  1. I think compacity is the most important thing of a checkpoint, that's why I don't merge ANY LORA in GhostMix. Checkpoint solves the CAN DO problem and Lora solves the DO IT RIGHT problem. （我认为checkpoint最终要的是兼容性，所以我没有融任何lora进checkpoint，checkpoint应该解决的是做的到的问题，而lora解决的是做的对的问题）

  2. Highres-Fix is A Must! Highres-Fix: 2x, denoising:0.4-0.5 or 1.5x, denoising:0.5-0.65. (一定要做高清修复! 高清修复: 2倍, 重绘幅度:0.4-0.5 或 1.5倍, 重绘幅度:0.5-0.65)

  4. Most Prompts in Previous Version of GhostMix can produce similiar result in New Version of GhostMix (之前用的大多数Prompts在新版本也可以生成相似的结果)

  5. Textual Inversion&VAE: ng_deepnegative_v1_75t and easynegative ,don't use Bad-Hand V4 & V5！（用 ng_deepnegative_v1_75t和easynegative,别用BadHandV4,V5)

  6. Sampler Suggest : DPM++ series , Steps: 20-30, CFG:5-7(7 is best)（采样方法建议 DPM++系列 , 步数20-30, CFG:5-7(7最好) ）

  7. Suggest resolution: 512,768! mechanical girl theme is very sensitive to the resolution, not suggest make the aspect ratio too low.(建议分辨率:512,768! 机械少女主题对分辨率设置非常敏感，不建议设太低的宽高比)

items.name: Rene Magritte Style
items.description:
René Magritte was a Belgian Surrealist artist known for his thought-provoking and enigmatic paintings. Born in 1898 in Belgium, Magritte's work challenged traditional notions of reality, often depicting ordinary objects in unexpected and surreal contexts.

Magritte's artistic style can be described as precise, detailed, and meticulously executed. He often painted with a realistic approach, using fine brushwork and smooth surfaces to create a sense of precision and clarity. However, what sets his work apart is the juxtaposition of ordinary objects and elements of fantasy, creating a sense of mystery and absurdity.

One of Magritte's most iconic techniques was his use of visual paradoxes and unexpected combinations. He frequently incorporated elements such as floating objects, obscured faces, and unexpected transformations to challenge the viewer's perception and invite them to question the nature of reality.

Magritte's subject matter often included everyday objects like bowler hats, pipes, and apples, but he imbued them with symbolic meaning and a sense of mystery. By placing these objects in unconventional settings or altering their proportions, he created a sense of ambiguity and invited viewers to interpret the deeper meanings behind his compositions.

Philosophical themes and symbolism were central to Magritte's work. He explored concepts of identity, perception, and the relationship between words and images. His paintings often engaged in witty and intellectual playfulness, challenging the viewer's assumptions and inviting them to reconsider the nature of representation and meaning.

Magritte's art continues to captivate audiences with its combination of visual allure and intellectual depth. His ability to blend the familiar with the strange, the ordinary with the extraordinary, makes his work both accessible and thought-provoking. His legacy as one of the most influential Surrealist artists remains strong, and his distinctive style and imagery continue to inspire and intrigue artists and viewers alike.
